        "content": "<p>Hello! I need to prove that the <code>{ m : ‚Ñ§ | f m ‚â• n }</code> is well-founded. The function <code>f</code> is strictly increasing, so the set is bounded below. Is there a lemma which lets me prove this by using the fact that natural numbers are well-founded? Or is there an easier way?</p>",
